{
  "text": "The present results indicate that hypothyroidism c a u s e s d y s f u n c t i on i n H P G a x i s a t t h e hypothalamic-pituitary level. The neuropeptide that regulates gonadal function at the hypothamicpituitary level is LHRH [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . There are several factors which inhibit LHRH secretion, and CRH is one of major factors for inhibiting it [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . In the present study, hypersecretion of CRH [CITATION_8] was confirmed in hypothyroid rats. Deficits in gonadal function at the hypothalamic-pituitary levels in hypothyroid rats may be mediated at least, partly, by CRH. ",
